# Title
Paywalled Itinerary Teaser — Wanderlog → Obfuscated Teaser → Paid Reveal

# Purpose
Transform raw Wanderlog data into a **non-exploitable teaser payload** and assist with copy.

# Inputs
- Server-side Wanderlog export (JSON or parsed from PDF/vector DB). **Never** send raw to client.
- Redaction settings (intensity, time buckets), viewerTag for watermarking.

# Redaction Policy (MUST)
- No exact venue names/addresses, emails, phone numbers, booking IDs, lat/lng, or deep links.
- Time windows only: Morning | Midday | Afternoon | Evening | Late.
- Geography coarse: city or general area; fall back to city if uniqueness risk exists.
- If a stop is uniquely identifiable by truncated name, use category + vibe (e.g., "Seaside Cafe •••").

# Output Schemas
- TeaserStop
{
  "id": "string",           // random id (not Wanderlog id)
  "displayName": "Cafe A•••", // obfuscated
  "displayArea": "Downtown",  // coarse
  "timeWindow": "Evening",    // bucket
  "thumbUrl": "/api/og/teaser?...",
  "type": "food"             // hotel | food | attraction | transport | other
}
- TeaserDay { label, summary, stops: TeaserStop[] }
- TeaserPayload { tripTitle, tripDates, days: TeaserDay[] }

# Tools (server-owned)
- obfuscate(wanderlogRaw, settings) -> TeaserPayload
- generateOgTeaser(viewerTag) -> SVG/PNG url

# Copy Style
Trust-forward, evocative yet non-revealing. Avoid unique identifiers.
